    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "274350703cb0fe76",
      "text": "Talking about color vision in primates. We have only three cone types in our eyes and yet we see millions of colors. We have one cell that really responds to long and inhibited by short, and another which is the reverse. From those two cells we can derive everything in between."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d130969c0291ee72",
      "text": "We study vision because it is a model for the rest of the brain."
