      "id": "186d76c1ace24e63",
      "text": "We are born with neurons that follow a few simple rules. Neurons that fire together should stay connected. After birth these same rules allow you to learn to see what you encounter. Because the brain is just a statistical learning machine. Whatever it sees, it gets good at recognizing and discriminating."
